ce
> income.  As a result of this provision, you will receive a refund of the
> extension payment.  The refund will be offset by the fact that the tax wa=
s
> paid in  2021.  However, the refund is over $600 and should be reported o=
n
> a final 2021 tax return.
>
>
>
>
>
> I would suggest that you set aside $1,000 to cover 2021 tax preparation
> fees. We will bill you for 2020 return preparation when the return is
> completed.  The draft 2020 Federal return shows a balance due of $2,206.
> The fact that the charity is only entitled to 70% of the trust residue
> means that the trust should only be able to deduct the 70% of the income
> allocable to the charity.  If the two of you were only getting specific
> bequests, all of the income would be allocable to charity.  It is a
> technical distinction and the split was not clear at the time of the
> extension.
